HEADWORD: Currycomb
<hw>Cur"ry*comb`</hw> <pr>(k?r"r?-k?m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind
of card or comb having rows of metallic teeth or serrated ridges, used
in currying a horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Currycomb</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Currycomb
<hw>Cur"ry*comb`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To comb with a
currycomb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curse</ent>⟦br⟧
